# Improvement Thinking

Common misconceptions:

children may believe:

```text id="p2e4qe"
first draft
=
finished writing
```

or:

```text id="u8e1qe"
editing
=
rewriting
everything
```

Some may:

```text id="c5e7qe"
focus
only
on spelling
```

without understanding:

```text id="k1e9qe"
revision
improves
ideas

editing
improves
correctness
```

Example:

students may:

```text id="n7e3qe"
fix commas
only
```

while ignoring:

```text id="t4e8qe"
unclear
ideas
or
organization
```

This skill teaches:

```text id="q6e2qe"
purposeful revision
```

For Grade 4:

focus includes:

Revision:

* clarity
* adding details
* organization
* stronger ideas
* removing confusion

Editing:

* spelling
* punctuation
* capitalization
* grammar
* proofreading

Important distinction:

```text id="a8e5qe"
revise
=
improve ideas

edit
=
correct mistakes
```

